import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values across budget years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    avg_values = data.groupby('budgetYear')['value'].mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=avg_values)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average value for each budget year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
